messageBody:
Hi Chuck,

Have you had a chance to look into the problem with character #8,
keyword "THey", in your dictionary? I've done a little more looking
and I was able to determine that in the QuikScript portion of the
dictionary character #8 (which is the capital "H" key in the
QuikScript fonts) only appears in one word, "GILKISONS". Is this
something you can correct? Or is this a problem with the source
dictionary that you translated your dictionary from?

Thanks,
Jeff

--- In Read_Alphabet@yahoogroups.com, Chuck Peck <chuck091956@o...> wrote:
> Hi Jeff,
>
> I never noticed that. You're right. Thanks for the catch. I guess
I'm going
> to have to take a re-look at the dictionary and correct that.
>
> Thanks,
> Chuck
>
>
> -----Original Message-----
> From: jeff_smith_8992 [mailto:jeff_smith_8992@y...]
> Sent: Wednesday, August 04, 2004 1:02 PM
> To: Read_Alphabet@yahoogroups.com
> Subject: [Read_Alphabet] Dictionary Definitions
>
>
> Hi Chuck,
>
> Here's a quick question... I noticed that in the dictionary you
> posted, the words, she and the, both start with the same QS symbol. Is
> this correct, or should "the" start with the "deep consonant", that
> extends below the bottom of the line (letter #8 in the QS manual)?
>
> Thanks,
> Jeff
